Problem Statement 1

Problem Statement

The consequences of traffic violation can be serious. You can face a stiff fine, traffic school, significantly higher insurance premiums, personal injury, death and possibly even the suspension of your driver's license. For instance, Speeding is one type of traffic violation. It endangers everyone on the road. In 2016 speeding killed 9,378 people. We all know the frustrations of modern life and juggling a busy schedule, but speed limits are put in place to protect all road users. Learn about the dangers of speeding and why faster does not mean safer.
